My #MentalHealth mantra? Feelings aren’t facts. They’re real, but just because I feel it, doesn’t mean it’s true. 

#MentalHealthActionDay 
#MentalHealthMonth

Tending to your mental health doesn’t have to be elaborate. Sometimes it’s just taking care of your basic needs.

Watch @sullivangrams’s full interview on our YouTube channel at the link in our profile.

Chris’ experience is just one of eight stories we are sharing this month to highlight the varying ways that self-love has manifested for different people. There is no one right way to take care of yourself and figuring out what works for you can require time, patience, and commitment. You’re not alone in this exploration.

Michael McGrath and I shared a dressing room for 14 months performing in Nice Work If You Can Get It. 

I learned incredible lessons in those 14 months about what it meant to be a theater professional, a committed clown, a loyal friend and an excellent father. 

He was a brilliant performer and I can’t believe he’s gone.

My takeaways from listening to @jazzy_joness and Ron’s closest lifelong friends…?

1. Ron Cephas Jones may have been the most self-realized man I have ever had the pleasure of knowing. And BY knowing himself so clearly, he could dedicate his life fully to his family, his friends and his art. 

2. Ron made his daughter feel loved and safe, by making space for her to fully express and realize HERself. In one memorial, I discovered everything I want to be as a father. 

#ripkingcephas
